1
00:00:06,090 --> 00:00:11,011
Are you now convinced
that Sam Ignacio didn't commit suicide?

2
00:00:11,095 --> 00:00:13,931
That there's a deeper truth to this case?

3
00:00:20,354 --> 00:00:21,897
Matt, I need you.

4
00:00:21,981 --> 00:00:24,692
-We need you.
-You said you got rid of it, didn't you?

5
00:00:24,775 --> 00:00:28,904
The sooner you tell them,
the sooner things will get easier.

6
00:00:28,988 --> 00:00:31,699
So, you aren't dismissing
the possibility of foul play?

7
00:00:31,782 --> 00:00:34,660
We aren't dismissing any possibilities.

8
00:00:34,744 --> 00:00:36,620
It looks like Sam's death
wasn't a suicide after all.

9
00:00:36,704 --> 00:00:38,205
Does that mean she was killed?

10
00:00:38,289 --> 00:00:39,498
You're working out this late?

11
00:00:40,791 --> 00:00:42,918
I'm just looking for someone
to fill a vacant position

12
00:00:43,002 --> 00:00:44,170
at the Able Hearts Foundation.

13
00:00:44,253 --> 00:00:46,088
You're the one I thought of.

14
00:00:46,172 --> 00:00:49,216
If you are one of the people
whose lives she touched,

15
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:51,427
please don't accept the assumption

16
00:00:51,510 --> 00:00:54,346
that she chose to end her story
by giving up.

17
00:00:55,931 --> 00:00:57,641
Sam didn't get to complete that.

18
00:00:57,725 --> 00:01:01,145
Or someone pulled strings to stop her.

19
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:17,411
Anton.

20
00:01:17,495 --> 00:01:18,454
Hon?

21
00:01:20,039 --> 00:01:21,499
Can we still use this?

22
00:01:22,124 --> 00:01:24,126
Yes, of course. It's still sturdy.

23
00:01:24,210 --> 00:01:26,796
It just needs a little fixing,
then it'll be as good as new.

24
00:01:27,755 --> 00:01:30,966
Isn't it a bit early, though?

25
00:01:31,050 --> 00:01:33,385
We just found out yesterday
that I'm pregnant.

26
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:36,096
Of course, I'm excited.

27
00:01:36,806 --> 00:01:38,557
I'm excited to be a father of three.

28
00:01:39,767 --> 00:01:40,976
You really are something.

29
00:01:42,686 --> 00:01:43,729
There.

30
00:01:44,563 --> 00:01:47,900
Isn't that what you've always wanted?

31
00:01:47,983 --> 00:01:49,568
Three kids, right?

32
00:01:52,905 --> 00:01:56,575
We could just buy a new one.
We can afford it now.

33
00:01:56,659 --> 00:01:58,118
No need.

34
00:01:58,202 --> 00:01:59,912
Think about it.

35
00:02:00,454 --> 00:02:03,874
All three of our kids using the same crib.

36
00:02:03,958 --> 00:02:06,001
Isn't that very meaningful?

37
00:02:07,419 --> 00:02:08,420
That's true.

38
00:02:10,005 --> 00:02:11,966
But you know what's even more meaningful?

39
00:02:12,758 --> 00:02:17,888
Raising our three kids to be good people.

40
00:02:18,889 --> 00:02:21,100
That's what we'll make sure of.

41
00:02:35,197 --> 00:02:38,450
-Want a snack?
-Yeah, I'm hungry.

42
00:02:38,534 --> 00:02:39,743
-Okay.
-Let me finish this.

43
00:02:39,827 --> 00:02:41,036
I'll make you something.

44
00:02:55,259 --> 00:02:56,343
Where were you?

45
00:02:58,220 --> 00:02:59,179
Just getting some air.

46
00:03:10,983 --> 00:03:11,984
Anton…

47
00:03:12,776 --> 00:03:17,031
The mayor's political advisor,
Atty. Cuizon.

48
00:03:18,157 --> 00:03:20,200
You were friends in law school, right?

49
00:03:21,493 --> 00:03:22,870
Yes, why?

50
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:27,458
Do you think he's noticed
anything unusual about the mayor?

51
00:03:30,377 --> 00:03:31,378
I don't know.

52
00:03:31,462 --> 00:03:34,131
It's been a long time
since we last saw each other.

53
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:37,343
And even if he has, I doubt he'd tell me.

54
00:03:38,969 --> 00:03:39,970
Why are you asking?

55
00:03:41,388 --> 00:03:42,431
Is there a problem?

56
00:03:49,647 --> 00:03:52,358
You think the mayor
had a hand in Sam's death?

57
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:56,320
And her brother, Ted Ignacio,
is connected to it?

58
00:03:57,446 --> 00:04:00,532
The siblings had some disagreements.

59
00:04:00,616 --> 00:04:02,868
Sam once mentioned to me that…

60
00:04:04,203 --> 00:04:07,915
she didn't like whatever
Ted got involved in

61
00:04:08,499 --> 00:04:10,209
since he came back here.

62
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:12,252
What was he involved in?

63
00:04:13,462 --> 00:04:14,588
I don't know.

64
00:04:15,339 --> 00:04:18,425
She never got to say.
She didn't want to talk about it.

65
00:04:18,509 --> 00:04:20,177
But I think

66
00:04:20,678 --> 00:04:25,140
Ted going into hiding might have
something to do with those files.

67
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:27,601
The other day,

68
00:04:29,561 --> 00:04:31,897
I saw Ted take something from Sam's house.

69
00:04:32,398 --> 00:04:34,900
It was in a bag,
hidden in the wood-fired oven.

70
00:04:35,401 --> 00:04:38,445
From what I could tell,
it was hundreds of thousands in cash.

71
00:04:38,529 --> 00:04:41,156
I think that's connected

72
00:04:42,157 --> 00:04:45,494
to Ted getting shot and Sam's death.

73
00:04:47,413 --> 00:04:50,290
Ma'am, we need to be careful.

74
00:04:52,876 --> 00:04:55,587
You can't tell a soul about this.

75
00:06:25,594 --> 00:06:26,678
Matteo?

76
00:06:39,566 --> 00:06:43,862
Matteo, where are you? Matteo?

77
00:07:00,712 --> 00:07:02,214
Classic Matteo.

78
00:07:34,913 --> 00:07:36,373
She's taking forever.

79
00:07:43,922 --> 00:07:45,340
What took you so long?

80
00:07:51,889 --> 00:07:53,557
I thought you already had an abortion.

81
00:07:56,894 --> 00:07:58,604
I couldn't.

82
00:07:59,605 --> 00:08:02,524
I can't hurt our baby.

83
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:08,405
But why did you have to lie to me?

84
00:08:09,615 --> 00:08:10,741
Jem, come on.

85
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:13,076
Because I got scared, babe.

86
00:08:13,827 --> 00:08:15,787
When I told you my period was late,

87
00:08:16,705 --> 00:08:18,540
I felt how scared you were.

88
00:08:19,124 --> 00:08:21,126
Especially when the test
came back positive.

89
00:08:21,210 --> 00:08:23,712
Then, you got mad
when Teacher Sam found out.

90
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:30,052
Sometimes, I don't even know
how to talk to you anymore.

91
00:08:30,135 --> 00:08:34,097
If you're not angry, you're cold.

92
00:08:35,349 --> 00:08:39,770
I feel like you're drifting
further and further away.

93
00:08:40,479 --> 00:08:41,438
Like…

94
00:08:41,939 --> 00:08:44,316
Like I'm about to lose you.

95
00:08:56,036 --> 00:08:57,162
Can we…

96
00:08:58,163 --> 00:09:00,040
Can we just keep this between us for now?

97
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:03,835
I just need some time to think.

98
00:09:10,926 --> 00:09:12,302
Sorry, I have to go home.

99
00:09:55,554 --> 00:09:57,472
Well, look who decided to come home.

100
00:09:58,223 --> 00:09:59,266
I almost didn't.

101
00:10:03,812 --> 00:10:05,731
But I didn't have a choice.

102
00:10:09,985 --> 00:10:12,195
It's okay for you to go out and drink,

103
00:10:12,779 --> 00:10:14,656
but you should at least let me know.

104
00:10:15,407 --> 00:10:16,992
Let it go, Pa.

105
00:10:19,244 --> 00:10:20,537
It's Mama's birthday.

106
00:10:22,873 --> 00:10:25,375
I knew it. You forgot.

107
00:10:28,712 --> 00:10:30,422
Even back then…

108
00:10:31,715 --> 00:10:35,218
work was always more important
than Mama and me.

109
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,555
That's not true.

110
00:11:44,287 --> 00:11:47,332
Matteo. Let's talk.

111
00:11:58,343 --> 00:11:59,428
Where were you?

112
00:12:00,679 --> 00:12:01,847
I…

113
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:05,559
just finished some
important schoolwork, Pa.

114
00:12:07,936 --> 00:12:09,187
Is that really all?

115
00:12:09,271 --> 00:12:13,358
Because lately, we've noticed
that you've been quiet and distracted.

116
00:12:13,442 --> 00:12:15,652
It's like you're not yourself anymore.

117
00:12:16,403 --> 00:12:17,654
Plus, you've been so distant from us.

118
00:12:19,781 --> 00:12:22,117
Is there something
your mother and I need to know?

119
00:12:26,204 --> 00:12:27,497
Matt…

120
00:12:27,998 --> 00:12:30,000
You need to talk to us,

121
00:12:31,042 --> 00:12:33,128
so we can help you.

122
00:12:33,211 --> 00:12:34,880
What's the problem?

123
00:12:36,047 --> 00:12:38,341
Nothing, Ma. Just school stuff.

124
00:12:38,884 --> 00:12:41,428
Well, do you need our help?

125
00:12:42,304 --> 00:12:44,014
No, I'm okay. I can handle it.

126
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:46,850
Matteo, we're here for you, okay?

127
00:12:47,392 --> 00:12:48,977
Just tell us.

128
00:12:52,564 --> 00:12:53,940
Have you eaten?

129
00:12:54,691 --> 00:12:55,692
Yes, Ma.

130
00:12:56,193 --> 00:12:57,402
I'll just go change, Pa.

131
00:13:17,297 --> 00:13:18,632
What are you doing here?

132
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:24,846
Matteo, did you get Jem pregnant?

133
00:13:31,061 --> 00:13:32,062
What?

134
00:13:33,063 --> 00:13:34,689
No. That's not true.

135
00:13:37,442 --> 00:13:38,777
Then what's this, Matteo?

136
00:13:39,736 --> 00:13:41,363
Matteo, what's this?

137
00:13:44,157 --> 00:13:46,451
Why do you have this?
Why are you messing with my stuff?

138
00:13:46,535 --> 00:13:48,370
So, it's true?

139
00:13:49,204 --> 00:13:50,872
Matteo, did you get Jem pregnant?

140
00:13:51,706 --> 00:13:52,707
Matteo!

141
00:13:56,211 --> 00:13:58,922
Well? Do Mama and Papa already know?

142
00:13:59,965 --> 00:14:00,799
No.

143
00:14:01,967 --> 00:14:03,260
Pia…

144
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:07,639
Pia.

145
00:14:08,306 --> 00:14:09,933
I need to ask you a favor, okay?

146
00:14:11,017 --> 00:14:13,436
Please, can you not say anything
to Mama and Papa?

147
00:14:14,437 --> 00:14:16,565
I'll tell them myself. I just need time.

148
00:14:30,453 --> 00:14:33,832
I'm here for you, Matteo.
I'm here for you.

149
00:14:49,848 --> 00:14:51,016
Alright.

150
00:15:19,544 --> 00:15:21,171
-There they are.
-We got the noodles!

151
00:15:22,672 --> 00:15:24,424
We brought noodles!

152
00:15:24,507 --> 00:15:26,509
-Wow!
-Let's eat!

153
00:15:26,593 --> 00:15:28,261
-Nice!
-That looks good.

154
00:15:28,345 --> 00:15:29,638
Come on, let's eat.

155
00:15:29,721 --> 00:15:31,723
It seems you're all happy
that I'm leaving.

156
00:15:31,806 --> 00:15:33,058
-No, sir.
-Of course not, sir.

157
00:15:33,141 --> 00:15:34,768
-We prepared this for you.
-Let's take a picture.

158
00:15:45,528 --> 00:15:48,782
Boys, we can't eat yet.
We have to wait for the mayor.

159
00:15:49,574 --> 00:15:52,911
-Bummer. I'm already hungry.
-Back to work. Come on!

160
00:15:54,663 --> 00:15:55,705
Policarpio.

161
00:15:56,539 --> 00:15:59,918
I'm still waiting for the files
on the robbery at the town proper.

162
00:16:00,001 --> 00:16:02,420
I'm on it, sir. Excuse me.

163
00:16:05,590 --> 00:16:07,842
Guys, do your job well.

164
00:16:07,926 --> 00:16:10,762
Make a good impression on the mayor.
Don't disappoint me.

165
00:16:46,339 --> 00:16:47,590
I was just thinking…

166
00:16:47,674 --> 00:16:51,469
Maybe we can go out of town next weekend.

167
00:17:05,984 --> 00:17:08,194
Okay, fine.

168
00:17:23,668 --> 00:17:24,502
Matt?

169
00:17:27,797 --> 00:17:29,048
Sure, Pa.

170
00:17:30,842 --> 00:17:32,218
Just a short break.

171
00:17:32,302 --> 00:17:35,555
We need that after everything
that has happened.

172
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:39,893
Hon?

173
00:17:47,442 --> 00:17:51,863
I think going out of town is a good idea.

174
00:17:51,946 --> 00:17:55,742
It'll be good for our family,
especially Eli.

175
00:19:12,235 --> 00:19:13,111
Anton.

176
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,786
If you need anything, call me.

177
00:19:21,870 --> 00:19:24,080
-Okay?
-Okay.

178
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:29,502
Ma, I'll just check on Eli later.

179
00:19:31,379 --> 00:19:33,756
See you later.

180
00:19:41,139 --> 00:19:42,140
Bye, Pa.

181
00:19:53,902 --> 00:19:55,069
Jackie.

182
00:19:55,153 --> 00:19:58,364
I'm glad people are no longer
putting the heat on Anton.

183
00:19:59,032 --> 00:20:02,243
I mean, this case is really shocking.

184
00:20:02,952 --> 00:20:04,495
So, who is it really?

185
00:20:04,579 --> 00:20:07,707
Was it really Sam's brother who killed her

186
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:11,044
or is someone else going after them?

187
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:14,130
It's so confusing.

188
00:20:15,924 --> 00:20:18,676
By the way, the dean wants to talk to us

189
00:20:18,760 --> 00:20:20,178
about something important.

190
00:20:20,261 --> 00:20:21,262
I'll follow in a bit.

191
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:43,576
Ma'am Jackie.

192
00:20:45,328 --> 00:20:48,790
I just want to ask you
if you know anything about Ted Ignacio

193
00:20:48,873 --> 00:20:50,875
that can help with the investigation.

194
00:20:53,086 --> 00:20:56,547
I don't know him
except that he's Sam's brother.

195
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:01,052
Sam didn't mention
anything about Ted either.

196
00:21:01,761 --> 00:21:03,763
Weren't they close as siblings?

197
00:21:03,846 --> 00:21:06,808
Ted would come and go in Sam's life.

198
00:21:06,891 --> 00:21:08,768
But I remember

199
00:21:08,851 --> 00:21:13,690
Sam told me that Ted showed up more often

200
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:15,775
ever since the Able Hearts Foundation
was established.

201
00:21:17,026 --> 00:21:21,489
But based on the information I gathered,
Ted has nothing to do with that NGO.

202
00:21:21,572 --> 00:21:24,993
But it's possible
he's connected with the mayor.

203
00:21:25,743 --> 00:21:27,870
Whatever their connection is…

204
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:31,082
that's what we'll find out.

205
00:21:31,165 --> 00:21:33,584
I have to go, Ma'am Jackie.
That's all. Thank you.

206
00:21:53,771 --> 00:21:57,442
I told you I'll only talk with you
once my lawyer is here.

207
00:21:59,819 --> 00:22:02,113
I think I earned the right
to interrogate you

208
00:22:02,196 --> 00:22:03,990
after you hit me last time.

209
00:22:04,073 --> 00:22:07,285
It's only normal I'd be cautious
after what happened to my sister.

210
00:22:07,994 --> 00:22:11,039
I don't know you,
and you showed up at our house.

211
00:22:11,122 --> 00:22:15,251
Yes, your house that you haven't lived in
for a long time.

212
00:22:16,002 --> 00:22:18,046
I went there to investigate.

213
00:22:18,129 --> 00:22:20,757
What about you? What were you doing there?

214
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:26,637
My sister died.
What's wrong about me being there?

215
00:22:31,225 --> 00:22:32,351
Nothing.

216
00:22:33,519 --> 00:22:35,396
But I saw you…

217
00:22:36,147 --> 00:22:42,320
take a bag with money
hidden inside a brick oven.

218
00:22:42,403 --> 00:22:44,072
Is that yours?

219
00:22:44,655 --> 00:22:45,990
Or was it Sam's?

220
00:22:48,534 --> 00:22:50,036
And most importantly…

221
00:22:52,663 --> 00:22:54,248
who is it from?

222
00:22:55,917 --> 00:22:59,337
The bullet that hit you
wasn't from the police.

223
00:23:00,421 --> 00:23:01,923
So, Ted…

224
00:23:03,424 --> 00:23:05,593
Is someone after you?

225
00:23:11,349 --> 00:23:12,683
Okay. How about this?

226
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:19,107
Does this have anything to do
with Sam's death?

227
00:23:21,692 --> 00:23:24,862
You had a lot to say earlier,
but now you're suddenly quiet.

228
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:31,202
Don't you want to get justice
for your sister's death?

229
00:23:44,048 --> 00:23:46,300
Or maybe you were the one who pushed her.

230
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:05,486
-We should focus on drug awareness.
-Is that what our teacher said?

231
00:24:05,570 --> 00:24:09,031
-Yeah, I think it'll come up.
-Let's highlight it.

232
00:24:09,115 --> 00:24:10,616
Hey, Matteo.

233
00:24:11,409 --> 00:24:12,827
Have you reviewed already?

234
00:24:12,910 --> 00:24:15,163
Where have you been?
We've been waiting for you.

235
00:24:15,246 --> 00:24:17,248
-Sit down.
-Come, join us.

236
00:24:17,331 --> 00:24:18,708
Sit here beside me.

237
00:24:19,208 --> 00:24:21,335
So about drug addiction…

238
00:24:21,419 --> 00:24:22,795
Matteo!

239
00:24:22,879 --> 00:24:25,756
Let's discuss how to avoid it.

240
00:24:26,549 --> 00:24:29,051
Here. It's about drug addiction.

241
00:24:29,135 --> 00:24:30,970
Dude, I have to go.

242
00:24:33,806 --> 00:24:35,057
He left.

243
00:24:35,141 --> 00:24:37,143
Let's study by ourselves, then.

244
00:24:45,818 --> 00:24:47,486
Thank you for coming, Mayor.

245
00:24:47,570 --> 00:24:50,156
I am so honored you're here.

246
00:24:50,239 --> 00:24:51,657
Thanks, Reden.

247
00:24:54,327 --> 00:24:56,537
By the way, before anything else,

248
00:24:56,621 --> 00:25:01,459
I would like to thank all of you
for your service to the town of Escondido.

249
00:25:02,043 --> 00:25:06,505
But most of all,
I would like to thank Chief Reden

250
00:25:07,048 --> 00:25:10,551
for his years of service
to the town of Escondido

251
00:25:10,635 --> 00:25:12,970
as a pillar of the police force.

252
00:25:13,054 --> 00:25:16,307
Escondido is one
of the most peaceful towns

253
00:25:16,390 --> 00:25:19,227
in our province,
and in the region as well.

254
00:25:27,151 --> 00:25:28,444
Thank you.

255
00:25:30,655 --> 00:25:32,156
I just have one request, Mayor.

256
00:25:32,782 --> 00:25:34,951
Can you please announce…

257
00:25:35,952 --> 00:25:37,870
the name of my successor?

258
00:25:41,874 --> 00:25:46,295
The Regional Office just released the memo

259
00:25:46,379 --> 00:25:49,674
regarding the new police chief
of the town of Escondido.

260
00:25:55,179 --> 00:25:57,515
Lieutenant Colonel Cortez!

261
00:26:04,355 --> 00:26:07,692
You are the new police chief of Escondido.

262
00:26:23,249 --> 00:26:24,542
Cortez.

263
00:26:29,380 --> 00:26:31,757
I'm leaving you in charge here.

264
00:26:43,811 --> 00:26:47,565
I know you'll do your best
to serve Escondido.

265
00:27:04,123 --> 00:27:05,499
Thank you.

266
00:27:15,426 --> 00:27:17,470
-Bro.
-Bro.

267
00:27:18,054 --> 00:27:20,181
How are things there
at the Regional Office?

268
00:27:21,849 --> 00:27:23,184
Wait.

269
00:27:23,267 --> 00:27:25,519
Congratulations, Chief!

270
00:27:26,979 --> 00:27:28,606
That's what I want to ask you.

271
00:27:30,358 --> 00:27:32,610
How did that happen?
I thought I'd just be an OIC.

272
00:27:32,693 --> 00:27:34,445
How come it was a full appointment?

273
00:27:34,528 --> 00:27:36,238
We just found out earlier.

274
00:27:36,322 --> 00:27:38,574
I heard it was the mayor's orders.

275
00:27:39,950 --> 00:27:42,578
-You mean Mayor Dominguez?
-Yes.

276
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:45,122
He's a very influential person.

277
00:27:45,206 --> 00:27:47,583
You showed off, didn't you?

278
00:27:47,666 --> 00:27:48,834
I have to go. That's all.

279
00:27:48,918 --> 00:27:50,127
-Thanks, man.
-Bye.

280
00:27:57,176 --> 00:27:58,511
Thank you for the recommendation.

281
00:27:59,345 --> 00:28:00,930
Your credentials are impressive.

282
00:28:01,472 --> 00:28:04,600
I know you can contribute
to the development of Escondido.

283
00:28:06,143 --> 00:28:07,645
You see…

284
00:28:09,063 --> 00:28:12,108
My vision for the town of Escondido

285
00:28:12,191 --> 00:28:14,693
is to make it a prime destination

286
00:28:15,945 --> 00:28:18,656
for family, for leisure…

287
00:28:18,739 --> 00:28:21,117
I want to make it family-oriented.

288
00:28:22,076 --> 00:28:24,370
Well, I heard that…

289
00:28:24,453 --> 00:28:29,542
a company wants to build
a casino resort here.

290
00:28:34,588 --> 00:28:38,509
That's why it's important
to have peace and order.

291
00:28:39,176 --> 00:28:40,803
Zero crime rate.

292
00:28:40,886 --> 00:28:46,475
I need someone like you
who is good and sharp.

293
00:28:46,559 --> 00:28:51,522
Someone who can clean up a mess
even before it spreads.

294
00:28:55,776 --> 00:28:57,027
Let's celebrate.

295
00:29:01,031 --> 00:29:03,826
We received a report
about students fighting at the plaza.

296
00:29:03,909 --> 00:29:05,661
Things got heated
during their basketball game.

297
00:29:05,744 --> 00:29:06,996
Has someone responded?

298
00:29:07,788 --> 00:29:09,123
But, sir,

299
00:29:09,206 --> 00:29:12,293
your son, Kyle Cortez,
was involved in that fight.

300
00:29:17,715 --> 00:29:18,674
Excuse me, Mayor.

301
00:29:41,113 --> 00:29:42,198
Well?

302
00:29:44,033 --> 00:29:46,368
When will you stop humiliating me?

303
00:29:47,620 --> 00:29:48,913
What do you want?

304
00:29:49,497 --> 00:29:50,956
I told you already, Pa.

305
00:29:52,082 --> 00:29:53,834
I want to go back to Manila.

306
00:29:55,169 --> 00:29:56,587
You think you can live alone?

307
00:29:57,713 --> 00:29:59,298
Can you provide for yourself?

308
00:29:59,381 --> 00:30:02,301
It's not like you're keeping
an eye on me here.

309
00:30:02,384 --> 00:30:04,470
You're always busy, right?

310
00:30:04,553 --> 00:30:07,431
You're always out investigating a case.

311
00:30:07,515 --> 00:30:08,933
You're always chasing someone!

312
00:30:09,725 --> 00:30:11,101
Even back then!

313
00:30:13,395 --> 00:30:15,439
Isn't that why you neglected Mama?

314
00:30:22,947 --> 00:30:25,032
You don't know what you're talking about.

315
00:30:29,078 --> 00:30:32,164
I'm right, aren't I, Pa?

316
00:30:35,751 --> 00:30:38,337
Where were you when Mama died?

317
00:30:53,477 --> 00:30:56,230
Here's what our teacher
wants us to review.

318
00:30:56,313 --> 00:30:59,149
From page 108 to…

319
00:31:00,901 --> 00:31:02,152
Page-- Wait.

320
00:31:02,236 --> 00:31:04,405
72 to 75.

321
00:31:05,239 --> 00:31:06,949
That's what we need to review.

322
00:31:08,909 --> 00:31:11,120
It'll be on the exam.

323
00:31:11,203 --> 00:31:12,913
Matteo, what's going on here?

324
00:31:12,997 --> 00:31:14,248
Keep your voice down.

325
00:31:14,331 --> 00:31:16,417
Why are you with that girl?

326
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:19,753
Excuse me? Can't you see
we're just writing a paper?

327
00:31:19,837 --> 00:31:21,922
Writing a paper or fooling around?

328
00:31:22,006 --> 00:31:24,466
-Keep your voice down.
-Ow! You're hurting me!

329
00:31:24,550 --> 00:31:26,010
-Matt!
-I'm hurting you?

330
00:31:27,761 --> 00:31:30,598
-I'm so sorry.
-Why are you apologizing to her?

331
00:31:30,681 --> 00:31:33,017
Jem, you're causing a scene.
Why are you shouting?

332
00:31:33,100 --> 00:31:34,435
-Come here.
-Ouch!

333
00:31:35,144 --> 00:31:36,770
-You're so annoying.
-I'm watching you.

334
00:31:36,854 --> 00:31:38,522
Let's talk about this calmly.

335
00:31:39,356 --> 00:31:41,066
Why are you blaming me?

336
00:31:41,150 --> 00:31:42,693
Matteo, let me go!

337
00:31:42,776 --> 00:31:44,653
-You're embarrassing me.
-It's her fault!

338
00:31:44,737 --> 00:31:46,488
I should have slapped that flirt!

339
00:31:46,572 --> 00:31:48,907
-Is she flirting with you?
-Stop causing a scene.

340
00:31:48,991 --> 00:31:51,118
It's her, right?

341
00:31:51,201 --> 00:31:53,120
She's the reason you became cold.

342
00:31:53,203 --> 00:31:55,789
Shut up. She's just a groupmate.

343
00:31:57,166 --> 00:31:59,168
You're calling me a liar?

344
00:31:59,251 --> 00:32:02,212
-Which one of us lied?
-Don't hold that over my head.

345
00:32:02,296 --> 00:32:04,214
You know why I did it.

346
00:32:09,928 --> 00:32:10,763
Fine.

347
00:32:11,263 --> 00:32:13,265
Fine. You want to know why I became cold?

348
00:32:13,849 --> 00:32:15,893
Because loving you is exhausting.

349
00:32:18,187 --> 00:32:20,147
I'm tired of apologizing

350
00:32:20,230 --> 00:32:22,941
every time you get jealous
when there's no reason to.

351
00:32:24,568 --> 00:32:26,362
I'm tired of explaining myself

352
00:32:27,112 --> 00:32:28,781
because of your suspicions.

353
00:32:28,864 --> 00:32:31,659
For crying out loud, Jem,
what do you want from me?

354
00:32:31,742 --> 00:32:35,704
I tell you everything,
where I am and what I'm doing.

355
00:32:35,788 --> 00:32:37,247
What more do you want?

356
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:43,212
Matteo, I only did it because I love you.

357
00:32:43,295 --> 00:32:44,296
"Love"?

358
00:32:46,590 --> 00:32:48,634
Babe, you love me too, don't you?

359
00:32:48,717 --> 00:32:49,677
Right, babe?

360
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,136
Babe, I'm going to change.

361
00:32:51,220 --> 00:32:53,138
-I'm going to change.
-Leave me alone.

362
00:32:53,222 --> 00:32:54,556
Babe, wait.

363
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:55,849
I'm going to change.

364
00:32:55,933 --> 00:32:57,393
I won't be jealous anymore.

365
00:32:58,143 --> 00:33:00,104
I won't doubt you anymore, I promise.

366
00:33:00,187 --> 00:33:02,523
Jem, what don't you understand?

367
00:33:03,816 --> 00:33:06,402
I'm saying I don't love you anymore.

368
00:33:08,529 --> 00:33:10,030
I'm done.

369
00:33:16,203 --> 00:33:18,372
-Jem, enough.
-You love me, don't you?

370
00:33:20,082 --> 00:33:21,375
-Not anymore!
-Wait, babe.

371
00:33:21,458 --> 00:33:23,752
If you're mad at me because I lied--

372
00:33:23,836 --> 00:33:25,754
Jem, I've just been putting up with you!

373
00:33:26,755 --> 00:33:27,965
Can't you see that?

374
00:33:32,010 --> 00:33:34,096
Just hearing your voice
gives me a headache.

375
00:33:34,179 --> 00:33:36,098
You're so demanding!

376
00:33:38,559 --> 00:33:41,770
All I hear from you is,
"Babe, do this, do that."

377
00:33:41,854 --> 00:33:43,939
"Babe, where are you?
Why aren't you replying?"

378
00:33:44,022 --> 00:33:45,566
I'm sick of it.

379
00:33:45,649 --> 00:33:49,361
Even my mother doesn't treat me that way.
What makes you think you can?

380
00:33:49,445 --> 00:33:51,363
So please, leave me alone. We're through.

381
00:33:51,447 --> 00:33:52,740
I don't love you anymore.

382
00:33:53,657 --> 00:33:56,493
Babe, what about our baby?

383
00:33:59,872 --> 00:34:01,248
Let me go.

384
00:34:04,168 --> 00:34:06,545
Babe, our baby…

385
00:34:07,755 --> 00:34:09,923
I'll take responsibility
if you want to keep it.

386
00:34:13,093 --> 00:34:14,928
I'll take responsibility for the child.

387
00:34:17,514 --> 00:34:18,974
But that's it.

388
00:34:20,476 --> 00:34:22,728
Don't expect anything else from me.

389
00:34:23,437 --> 00:34:24,354
We're through.

390
00:34:42,790 --> 00:34:45,292
I'm sorry. Your files are not enough.

391
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:48,420
How is that not enough?

392
00:34:48,504 --> 00:34:51,590
It's not substantial enough
to charge the mayor or anyone else.

393
00:34:52,591 --> 00:34:57,638
Detective, we both know
that the mayor is behind it all.

394
00:34:58,388 --> 00:35:01,266
The documents we have
don't have his signature.

395
00:35:02,267 --> 00:35:04,520
I wouldn't be surprised
if they're fabricated.

396
00:35:05,229 --> 00:35:06,522
What about the videos?

397
00:35:07,356 --> 00:35:09,525
I can go through them again.

398
00:35:09,608 --> 00:35:11,485
Maybe we missed something.

399
00:35:11,568 --> 00:35:14,738
I reviewed the videos closely.
They didn't mention anything.

400
00:35:15,572 --> 00:35:17,366
Mrs. Carpio, let me ask you this.

401
00:35:18,909 --> 00:35:21,745
How well did you know Sam Ignacio?

402
00:35:23,997 --> 00:35:26,708
How can you be sure
that everything she showed you

403
00:35:26,792 --> 00:35:28,836
and told you was true?

404
00:35:31,338 --> 00:35:32,548
Wait a minute.

405
00:35:35,425 --> 00:35:37,594
Why the change of tune…

406
00:35:39,429 --> 00:35:40,597
Chief?

407
00:35:42,808 --> 00:35:44,601
Is it because of your promotion?

408
00:35:47,896 --> 00:35:50,524
So now you're protecting the mayor?

409
00:35:53,318 --> 00:35:55,571
I'm just going on with what we have.

410
00:35:56,321 --> 00:35:59,616
This is all based
on what's inside that flash drive.

411
00:36:00,534 --> 00:36:02,744
I am not protecting anyone.

412
00:38:08,078 --> 00:38:09,454
Why did you meet?

413
00:38:10,163 --> 00:38:11,623
What did you talk about?

414
00:38:12,791 --> 00:38:14,251
Are you following me?

415
00:38:22,509 --> 00:38:23,719
Yes, Anton.

416
00:38:24,386 --> 00:38:26,346
I met with Detective Cortez.

417
00:38:26,430 --> 00:38:27,681
We talked.

418
00:38:29,516 --> 00:38:30,600
Anton.

419
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:34,229
I found evidence.

420
00:38:35,188 --> 00:38:37,649
Evidence that suggests

421
00:38:37,733 --> 00:38:40,610
that the mayor may have been
involved in Sam's death.

422
00:39:18,565 --> 00:39:19,483
Why do you look like that?

423
00:39:19,566 --> 00:39:21,485
Not now, Jem. I have a test in Poli Sci!

424
00:39:21,568 --> 00:39:23,570
What's this? Prof. Carpio
assigned a 4,000-word essay!

425
00:39:23,653 --> 00:39:24,946
I just want to let this out.

426
00:39:25,030 --> 00:39:26,239
Attention seeker.

427
00:39:26,323 --> 00:39:28,200
Let it all out.

428
00:39:29,117 --> 00:39:31,953
What's going on, Jem?
Screw the Poli Sci exam!

429
00:39:32,037 --> 00:39:34,623
Because I can't carry it anymore.

430
00:39:34,706 --> 00:39:36,041
What could it be this time?

431
00:39:36,708 --> 00:39:42,130
All of you tell me
that I'm lucky to be with Matteo.

432
00:39:43,423 --> 00:39:45,092
The enemy's getting closer.

433
00:39:45,592 --> 00:39:48,637
It's right next to you. Shoot it!

434
00:39:48,720 --> 00:39:50,806
Because he comes from a good family

435
00:39:50,889 --> 00:39:52,766
and he's the son of educators.

436
00:39:54,851 --> 00:39:57,187
Why didn't you tell me
where you were going?

437
00:39:57,270 --> 00:39:59,481
I found evidence.

438
00:39:59,564 --> 00:40:02,150
Would you rather I kept quiet?

439
00:40:02,234 --> 00:40:04,194
Why didn't you consult me?

440
00:40:04,277 --> 00:40:07,030
How could you trust that bastard Cortez?

441
00:40:07,114 --> 00:40:09,866
He is the only one
who cares about the truth.

442
00:40:09,950 --> 00:40:13,161
He doesn't believe
that Sam committed suicide.

443
00:40:13,245 --> 00:40:14,496
Says who?

444
00:40:15,247 --> 00:40:16,623
You believe them?

445
00:40:17,415 --> 00:40:18,917
But you're all wrong.

446
00:40:23,213 --> 00:40:25,465
He got me pregnant.

447
00:40:25,549 --> 00:40:28,844
Now, he's breaking up with me.

448
00:40:30,804 --> 00:40:32,180
On your right, bro.

449
00:40:32,264 --> 00:40:33,974
Come on, shoot it.

450
00:40:34,057 --> 00:40:35,308
I've got your back.

451
00:40:44,568 --> 00:40:45,735
Jackie.

452
00:40:46,278 --> 00:40:48,780
Do you think the truth even matters now?

453
00:40:48,864 --> 00:40:50,532
Sam is gone, Jackie.

454
00:40:51,408 --> 00:40:53,743
And there is a reason why it happened.

455
00:40:54,452 --> 00:40:56,371
What do you want, Jackie?

456
00:40:56,454 --> 00:40:58,331
For you to be their next target?

457
00:40:59,541 --> 00:41:01,084
You said it yourself.

458
00:41:01,168 --> 00:41:03,503
The evidence points to the mayor.

459
00:41:04,588 --> 00:41:07,674
Don't you realize the mess
you're getting yourself into?

460
00:41:07,757 --> 00:41:08,842
And now…

461
00:41:10,093 --> 00:41:11,761
Cortez has been promoted.

462
00:41:12,596 --> 00:41:14,848
He's probably under the mayor's thumb now.

463
00:41:14,931 --> 00:41:17,225
You're just putting our family in danger.

464
00:41:20,061 --> 00:41:22,355
Is that what you call an ideal boyfriend?

465
00:41:22,439 --> 00:41:24,941
Someone who hangs you out to dry?

466
00:41:26,109 --> 00:41:30,697
He's forcing me to abort our baby.

467
00:41:32,324 --> 00:41:34,034
But I can't do it.

468
00:41:34,117 --> 00:41:36,745
I can't abort our baby.

469
00:41:41,583 --> 00:41:42,751
Matteo!

470
00:41:42,834 --> 00:41:45,378
-There! At the corner!
-Matteo!

471
00:41:45,462 --> 00:41:46,504
Matteo!

472
00:41:47,839 --> 00:41:49,424
Matteo!

473
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:51,176
-Wait, bro. I'll be back.
-Matteo!

474
00:41:51,259 --> 00:41:52,427
Matteo!

475
00:41:54,763 --> 00:41:56,264
-Coming.
-Matteo!

476
00:41:58,141 --> 00:41:59,184
Matteo!

477
00:42:00,852 --> 00:42:01,728
Matteo!

478
00:42:02,812 --> 00:42:03,939
Matteo!

479
00:42:05,357 --> 00:42:06,316
Matteo!

480
00:42:06,399 --> 00:42:07,609
Pia, what's all this ruckus?

481
00:42:07,692 --> 00:42:09,486
My goodness, Pia. What's going on?

482
00:42:09,569 --> 00:42:10,612
Ma, Pa…

483
00:42:18,078 --> 00:42:21,456
Back then, I was so confused.

484
00:42:25,001 --> 00:42:26,378
I felt…

485
00:42:27,337 --> 00:42:29,297
I was all alone.

486
00:42:30,048 --> 00:42:31,258
And…

487
00:42:31,341 --> 00:42:34,678
And only one person could understand me.

488
00:42:36,763 --> 00:42:38,515
Teacher Sam.

489
00:42:39,140 --> 00:42:41,101
That's why I approached her.

490
00:42:42,352 --> 00:42:44,104
And she told us…

491
00:42:44,729 --> 00:42:48,316
to talk to our parents.

492
00:42:48,400 --> 00:42:50,443
But Matteo refused.

493
00:42:51,653 --> 00:42:56,032
He got mad at me for telling Teacher Sam.

494
00:42:57,659 --> 00:43:01,579
He was worried Teacher Sam
would tell his parents.

495
00:43:02,372 --> 00:43:03,540
That's why…

496
00:43:04,374 --> 00:43:09,462
Matteo and I met with Teacher Sam

497
00:43:10,380 --> 00:43:12,132
by the lighthouse.

498
00:43:13,425 --> 00:43:15,468
He asked her

499
00:43:16,469 --> 00:43:20,724
to keep my pregnancy a secret

500
00:43:20,807 --> 00:43:24,102
since he had already decided

501
00:43:24,853 --> 00:43:27,439
to abort the baby.

502
00:43:31,568 --> 00:43:33,445
-Matteo!
-But…

503
00:43:34,070 --> 00:43:36,489
-Teacher Sam refused.
-Matteo!

504
00:43:36,573 --> 00:43:40,535
She said
that if we don't tell our parents,

505
00:43:40,618 --> 00:43:42,454
she would tell them herself.

506
00:43:43,038 --> 00:43:45,290
Matteo was furious.

507
00:43:45,373 --> 00:43:47,250
He started screaming.

508
00:43:48,251 --> 00:43:51,546
He kept screaming until…

509
00:43:52,839 --> 00:43:53,923
Until…

510
00:43:54,674 --> 00:43:57,177
he wanted to hurt Teacher Sam.

511
00:44:01,139 --> 00:44:03,600
Back at the cliff…

512
00:44:04,768 --> 00:44:05,852
Matteo…

513
00:44:07,228 --> 00:44:08,855
Matteo pushed…

514
00:44:12,692 --> 00:44:15,445
He pushed Teacher Sam!

515
00:44:16,363 --> 00:44:17,489
Oh, God…

516
00:44:21,993 --> 00:44:23,745
That's not…

517
00:44:23,828 --> 00:44:24,829
No…

518
00:44:25,538 --> 00:44:26,539
Matteo!

519
00:44:27,290 --> 00:44:28,458
Matteo!

520
00:44:32,754 --> 00:44:33,838
Open the door!

521
00:44:53,900 --> 00:44:54,734
Pa.

522
00:44:57,278 --> 00:44:58,113
Matt…

523
00:44:58,196 --> 00:44:59,781
-Ma.
-No, Matt…

524
00:45:00,407 --> 00:45:01,282
Matt…

525
00:45:05,203 --> 00:45:06,746
Ma, I'm really sorry.

526
00:45:35,442 --> 00:45:37,861
We need to know everything
in order to help Matteo.

527
00:45:37,944 --> 00:45:39,612
Otherwise, you'll end up in jail!

528
00:45:39,696 --> 00:45:40,989
You're scaring him!

529
00:45:41,865 --> 00:45:44,451
-Just tell them I did it.
-No! No!

530
00:45:44,534 --> 00:45:45,910
No one is going to jail! No one!

531
00:45:45,994 --> 00:45:48,246
Do you understand? No one's going to jail!

532
00:45:49,789 --> 00:45:51,124
Good morning.

533
